          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Morino D'Souza"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-04-24",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "If you are planning to consider this school for the admission of your child, please DONT. I am an existing parent of this school and sharing my ongoing experience so that you take a better decision for your child.\n\n1. School has a policy that class teacher will never call parents and Parents can never call class teacher to discuss anything about the child. Even then if parents call class teacher, they do not pick the call.\n\n2. Class teacher writes incomplete homework in diary that too once a week\nOn asking about the homework of rest of the books they say you have to turn over the pages and find it on your own.\n\n3. In school bus, more than 50% of the days the assigned teacher will be absent. There are no phone numbers maintained of parents in the school bus. The teacher in the bus always on the phone\n\n4. School has a mandate to buy all books, school bag, uniform from the school. The quality of the school bag and uniform is very poor and for just one shirt school is charging 500-600 rupees.\n\n6. Class teacher wrongly checks the work done by children.\n\n7. Class teacher shows zero involvement with children. Once we went to school to personally talk to class teacher, she came only for 2 minutes. Means even if you visit the school you can't guarantee that you will get to meet the class teacher.\n\n8. Existing parent is never allowed to meet principal.",
